Airflow is a powerful platform that allows users to create and manage complex workflows. It offers a range of features such as task scheduling, monitoring, and dependencies management that make it a popular choice for data engineers and data scientists. However, when Airflow tasks fail or get stuck, it can disrupt the entire workflow, causing delays and impacting the overall productivity. Therefore, it is essential to know how to identify and fix these issues quickly to ensure that your workflows run smoothly and efficiently. In this guide, we will walk you through the steps to fix an Airflow task and get your workflow back on track.

3. Check if your name appears in the row. If it does, you are on duty for the day. You may also check the entire week's schedule from the table adjacent to it.
4. If you are on duty for the day, ensure that you are available to receive calls from Pager Duty. You can access Pager Duty at https://invent-analytics.pagerduty.com/users/PHCDT87 using the username and password provided by Alpha in LastPass. Update the phone section to ensure that you can be reached in case of any problems.
5. Once you are set up to receive calls, you will be notified if any tasks in the daily_dag fail. These failures may be caused by failures in other DAGs. To determine which task in which DAG has failed, check your email first, and then the relevant Slack channel if necessary.

Once you have identified the failed task, check the task logs to determine the cause of the failure. Once you have fixed the issue, retry the task. You can retry the task by clicking on the failed task in the DAG graph view and then clicking on the Clear button to clear the task's state.

Once a task has been cleared and has started running, it will be displayed as an open green box. If the task completes successfully, it will be outlined in dark green.

If a cluster of tasks have completed successfully and you wish to rerun a failed task, clear the failed task.

The "Upstream" option selects all tasks upstream of the selected task, while the "Downstream" option selects all tasks downstream of the selected task.
